The paper deals with the computational complexity of recognizing certain types of graphs, which is a topic that falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of path-k-coloring and the Cartesian product of graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and graph theory (cs.GT).
